user_location: of Redlight Redlight Beer Parlour & Brewery Orlando, Florida
review_blob: Sweet vanilla and oak on the nose. Pours slightly hazy blonde with little head in a Teku glass. Small streams of bubbles do cascade up though. Oak up front, chardonnay fruit flavors, fruit acidity as well as some lactic acidity comes through. Hints of vanilla and hints of tannin, smooth up front with some sharpness in the middle, but finishes smooth as well. Not overly acidic, grape must and oak balance the acidity well. Very nice.
